headline: 3 Healthcare Stocks to Keep an Eye On
summary: Personal health and wellness is one of the many secular tailwinds for healthcare companies. But financial performance has lagged recently as players offloaded surplus COVID inventories in 2023 and 2024, a headwind for overall demand. The result? Over the past six months, the industry has tumbled by 13%. This drop was worse than the S&P 500’s 5.5% loss.
